## Verification (how to test end-to-end)
Run inside the dev container (`devcon`), from repo root:
1. `python3 Testing/chirp_sysid/run_chirp_sysid.py --scenarios all --verify`
   — builds SITL, runs all 10 scenarios (≈10 gazebo boots, several minutes), writes
   `logs/<scenario>_<UTC>.ulg` + `.scenario.json`, then runs the verifier batch and exits nonzero
   if any scenario fails.
2. Expected verifier matrix: 5 positives + 3 timing = `chirp_present` PASS (corr ≳ 0.8, onset within
   1.5 s of the EN edge; timing onsets ≈ 2/5/10 s); `neg_armed_disabled` + `neg_unarmed_enabled` =
   `no_chirp` PASS.
3. Spot-check a plot: `python3 Testing/chirp_sysid/verify_chirp.py --ulog logs/pos_cyclic_pitch_*.ulg --plot out.png`
   then reopen with the picklable viewer; the sweep overlay should sit on the EN window and the
   shaded armed interval.
4. Sanity baseline (no SITL needed): the verifier already passes on the existing
   `logs/cyclic_pitch_20260603T164203Z.ulg` (validated: |corr|=0.905, EN edge at 2.90 s).

## Risks / notes
- **`rpm` mode (5)** injects into the motor channel, not the swashplate; the all-channel scan covers
  it but the 0.905 figure was on servos — the motor-channel corr is unvalidated and may sit lower.
  First live run may justify a per-mode threshold; `--threshold` is exposed.
- **Reboot persistence**: `SDLOG_MODE 2` must persist across the reboot — rely on param autosave /
  force a save before `MAV_CMD_PREFLIGHT_REBOOT_SHUTDOWN`; confirm the post-reboot ulog contains the
  disarmed window on the first run.
- **Runtime**: `--scenarios all` is ~10 boots; `--scenarios pos_cyclic_pitch,neg_armed_disabled`
  etc. remain available for quick iteration.
